eConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n**src/core/engine.ts (117 lines)** - The BuildEngine class:\n- `registerPlugin(plugin)` - Adds plugins to the engine\n- `registerTemplate(template)` - Registers templates for rendering\n- `resolvePluginOrder()` - Topological sort of plugins based on dependencies (detects circular and missing dependencies)\n- `build(files)` - Main build method that:\n  1. Calls all `beforeBuild` hooks in plugin order\n  2. Applies `transformContent` hooks to each file in plugin order\n  3. Renders templates for each file\n  4. Calls all `afterBuild` hooks in plugin order\n  5. Returns BuildContext with output and assets\n- `getPlugins()` and `getTemplates()` - Accessors\n\n**src/core/templates.ts (43 lines)** - Template factories:\n- `createDefaultTemplate()` - Returns a \"default\" template with basic HTML structure including title, date, content\n- `createListTemplate()` - Returns a \"list\" template for displaying lists with a div.list wrapper\n\n**src/core/index.ts (3 lines)** - Barrel export file exporting BuildEngine, template factories, and all types\n\n---\n\n### 4. All Test Files in tests/\n\n**tests/core.test.ts (195 lines)** - Core engine tests covering:\n- Plugin registration\n- Template registration\n- Building with default and list templates\n- Raw content output when no template matches\n- beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild hooks\n- Plugin dependency resolution and ordering\n- Circular dependency detection\n- Missing dependency detection\n- Multiple plugin transformContent applied in order\n- Shared data store in BuildContext\n- File metadata retention through build\n- Empty file list handling\n\n---\n\n### 5. All Plugin Test Files in tests/plugins/\n\n**tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts (108 lines)**\nTests for a plugin that rewrites relative asset URLs:\n- Rewrites `./image.png` to `/assets/image.png` in img src\n- Rewrites `./doc.pdf` to `/assets/doc.pdf` in href\n- Leaves absolute URLs unchanged\n- Generates asset-manifest in ctx.data with list of assets\n- Handles files with no assets\n- Handles multiple assets in one file\n- Doesn't double-process already-rewritten URLs\n\n**tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts (115 lines)**\nTests for search index generation plugin:\n- Generates search-index.json in ctx.output\n- Index entries have title, slug, and plain text content\n- Strips HTML tags from indexed content\n- Includes code blocks in searchable text\n- Handles empty file list\n- Produces valid JSON\n- Includes tags if present on files\n\n**tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts (91 lines)**\nTests for markdown processing with extensions:\n- Converts markdown (# headers, **bold**) to HTML\n- Handles footnotes with [^1] syntax, generates `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n- Renders footnote section at bottom: `<section class=\"footnotes\">`\n- Converts `:::note` container to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n- Converts `:::warning` and `:::tip` containers to admonition divs\n- Preserves existing HTML content\n- Handles empty content\n\n**tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts (127 lines)**\nTests for tag-based taxonomy/categorization:\n- Builds tag index from file tags in beforeBuild hook\n- Stores tag map as `taxonomy-tags` in ctx.data\n- Generates tag listing pages in ctx.output (e.g., `tags/javascript.html`)\n- Handles files with no tags\n- Handles files with multiple tags\n- Tag pages list all files with that tag\n- Normalizes tags to lowercase\n- Generates tag pages in afterBuild hook\n\n**tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts (96 lines)**\nTests for development server configuration:\n- Stores dev-server-config in ctx.data\n- Config includes port (default 3000)\n- Config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline plugin\n- Config includes search index path (/search-index.json)\n- Config includes content routes for HTML files\n- Handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\n**tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts (121 lines)**\nTests for RSS feed generation:\n- Generates valid RSS 2.0 XML with proper structure\n- Feed items contain HTML content wrapped in CDATA\n- Feed items include category tags from taxonomy\n- Channel title comes from config\n- Items sorted by date (newest first)\n- Handles files without dates\n- Feed link uses baseUrl from config\n- Item links use config baseUrl\n\n**tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts (102 lines)**\nTests for XML sitemap generation:\n- Generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output\n- Includes all content page URLs (e.g., `https://example.com/post-1.html`)\n- Includes taxonomy tag page URLs (e.g., `https://example.com/tags/javascript.html`)\n- Includes feed.xml URL\n- Uses baseUrl from config for all URLs\n- Valid XML structure with proper tags\n- Handles sites with no tag pages\n\n**tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts (108 lines)**\nTests for syntax highlighting:\n- Adds \"highlighted\" class to code blocks with language\n- Adds `data-language` attribute to pre tags (e.g., `data-language=\"python\"`)\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Handles code blocks without language specified (no modification)\n- Preserves code block content\n- Handles empty code blocks\n- Does not modify inline code in paragraphs\n\n---\n\n### 6. package.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` - TypeScript compilation\n- `npm run lint` - ESLint on src/ and tests/\n- `npm run test` - Run tests with vitest\n\n**Dependencies note:** Express and marked are available but not currently used in the codebase (likely for future plugins)\n\n---\n\n### 7. tsconfig.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration:**\n- Strict mode enabled for type safety\n- ES2022 target\n- CommonJS output with Node16 module resolution\n- Output to dist/ directory\n- Source in src/ directory\n- Declaration files (.d.ts) generated\n- Only compiles src/ files (tests are excluded)\n\n---\n\n###